The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Mamata letter
                                                                                                               Mamata letter
                            
	Calcutta, May 29: The state school education minister today wrote to railway minister Mamata Banerjee, finance minister Pranab Mukherjee and human resource development minister Kapil Sibal requesting them to look into the problems affecting 75,000 students of primary teachers training institutes held illegal by the high court.        
	Ive requested the central ministers to ensure that the National Council for Teachers Education works out something to help the 75,000 students whose degrees and diplomas have become invalid, Partha De said tonight.                                                                                                                                                                              
